        "category": "The Books",
        "content": "---\ntitle: Python for Cybersecurity\ntags: mitre, red-team, book\n---\n\n# Python for Cybersecurity\n\n279-page book mapping the MITRE ATT&CK framework to executable\nPython tradecraft. Each chapter covers one ATT&CK tactic and walks two concrete\ntechniques with working tooling, ending in a Summary and Suggested Exercises.\n\n## Coverage\n- 13 tactic chapters: Pre-ATT&CK, Initial Access, Execution, Persistence,\n  Privilege Escalation, Defense Evasion, Credential Access, Discovery,\n  Lateral Movement, Collection, Command & Control, Exfiltration, Impact.\n- Windows-centric: Registry autoruns, WMI, Event logs, logon types.\n\n## Where it fits\nThis book is the playbook layer. See [[mitre-attack-framework]] for the\nunderlying matrix, and [[initial-access]], [[persistence]], [[credential-access]],\n[[exfiltration]] for the tactics it implements in Python.\n\n## Related\n- [[mitre-attack-framework]]\n- [[initial-access]]\n- [[persistence]]\n- [[credential-access]]\n- [[exfiltration]]\n",
