        "category": "The Books",
        "content": "---\ntitle: Understanding Network Hacks (Ballmann)\ntags: scapy, protocols, book\n---\n\n# Understanding Network Hacks (Ballmann)\n\nBastian Ballmann's 187-page \"Attack and Defense with Python\"\n(Springer, 2015). Hands-on protocol-level hacking: every attack ships with a\nshort Python script and a matching detection/defense variant.\n\n## Coverage\n- Networking fundamentals (OSI, Ethernet, ARP, IP, TCP/UDP, firewalls, MITM).\n- Layer 2, TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP, WiFi, and Bluetooth attacks using raw sockets\n  and Scapy.\n- Appendix: Scapy reference.\n\n## Where it fits\nThis is the fundamentals + code layer. Built on [[scapy]] and\n[[python-sockets]]. Concrete techniques: [[arp-spoofing]], [[port-scanning]],\n[[dns-spoofing]], [[sql-injection]], [[wifi-attacks]], [[bluetooth-attacks]].\n\n## Related\n- [[scapy]]\n- [[python-sockets]]\n- [[arp-spoofing]]\n- [[port-scanning]]\n- [[dns-spoofing]]\n- [[sql-injection]]\n- [[wifi-attacks]]\n- [[bluetooth-attacks]]\n",
